- 📄 **View the PDF Report:** 

## 📈 Key Insights  
- 🔹 **Insight 1:** Expand High-Revenue Cuisine Offerings
High-revenue restaurants focus on pizza, American snacks, and street food.
Restaurants looking to boost sales should consider adding or emphasizing these items on their menus.  
- 🔹 **Insight 2:** Optimize Location-Based Strategy
Navrangpuri and Bareilly are revenue hotspots, particularly for Indian and dessert-based cuisines.
Restaurants should explore expansion into these cities if they serve similar food styles.
Electronic City, Bangalore, houses many of the most popular restaurants with Ice Cream and North Indian cuisines.
If operating in this area, restaurants should leverage seasonal offers and marketing campaigns to boost brand awareness and drive traffic.
- 🔹 **Insight 3:** Leverage Promotions to Increase Sales Volume
The highest revenue restaurant (Domino’s) has $5M in sales, while other high-revenue places are around $1.9M.
Promotional offers, bundle deals, and loyalty programs can drive up sales volume and boost revenue.


